Notation of primary setae and pores on larvae of Carabidae (Coleoptera: Adephaga)
Article
Full-text available
  • Feb 2011
  • Yves Bousquet
  • H. Goulet
Based on a study of more than 75 species of Carabidae and six species of other coleopterous families, the ancestral system of primary setae and pores on carabid larvae is established, described, and illustrated. Problems associated with homology of these setae and pores between species studied are discussed and some are illustrated.
